### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Register a new user
POST https://localhost:7001/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "address": "123 Test St, Test City"
}

### 2. Login with the registered user
POST https://localhost:7001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Login with sample admin user
POST https://localhost:7001/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@touristagency.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Get current user (replace TOKEN with actual token from login response)
GET https://localhost:7001/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test protected endpoint - Get destinations (should work without auth)
GET https://localhost:7001/api/destinations

### 6. Test protected endpoint - Get customers (should require auth)
GET https://localhost:7001/api/customers
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE